            ],
            "name": "param-Q3-RestAPI"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "*💡 REST APIs let Sentinel pull data programmatically. Most cloud services and SaaS platforms expose one.*"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q1",
                "comparison": "isNotEqualTo"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q2",
                "comparison": "isNotEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-HelpQ3"
          },
          {
            "type": 9,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
              "parameters": [
                {
                  "id": "7a93ea61-7d30-448c-9f71-6886dee30fd2",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "Q4a",
                  "label": "4️⃣a Is the Codeless Connector Framework (CCF) suitable?",
                  "type": 10,
                  "isRequired": true,
                  "typeSettings": {
                    "additionalResourceOptions": [],
                    "showDefault": false
                  },
                  "jsonData": "[{ \"value\": \"Yes\", \"label\": \"Yes\"},\r\n {\"value\": \"No\", \"label\": \"No\" }]",
                  "timeContext": {
                    "durationMs": 86400000
                  }
                }
              ],
              "style": "formVertical",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q3",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "param-Q4a-CCF"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "*💡 CCF works best with REST APIs that support pagination, return JSON, and use standard auth (OAuth2 or API key). No custom code required.*"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q3",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "text-HelpQ4a"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Use Codeless Connector Framework (CCF)\r\n\r\nThe CCF allows you to create a custom data connector for Microsoft Sentinel without writing code. Define a JSON configuration that tells Sentinel how to connect to your data source's REST API and ingest data.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Data source must expose a REST API with pagination support\r\n- OAuth2 or API key authentication\r\n- JSON response format\r\n\r\n🔗 [Create a codeless connector](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/create-codeless-connector)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has a REST API (Q3: {Q3}) and CCF is suitable (Q4a: {Q4a}). CCF is the preferred no-code approach for REST API sources — it runs natively in Sentinel with zero infrastructure.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- Logs Ingestion API would work but requires custom code to call the API and forward data\r\n- AMA-based methods (CEF/Syslog) don't apply — your source has a REST API, not log streaming\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Requires REST API with pagination support and JSON responses\r\n- Only supports OAuth2 and API key authentication (no SAML, no client certificate)\r\n- Not suitable for APIs with complex workflows, binary data, or non-standard pagination",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4a",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultCCF"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Use Logs Ingestion API\r\n\r\nThe Logs Ingestion API allows you to send data to a Log Analytics workspace from any REST client. This is the preferred method when a built-in connector or CCF is not available but the source has an API.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Data Collection Endpoint (DCE)\r\n- Data Collection Rule (DCR)\r\n- OAuth/RBAC authentication (Microsoft Entra app registration)\r\n\r\n🔗 [Logs Ingestion API overview](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/logs/logs-ingestion-api-overview)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has a REST API (Q3: {Q3}) but CCF isn't suitable (Q4a: {Q4a}). The Logs Ingestion API gives you full control with custom code to pull data and push it to Sentinel.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- CCF was ruled out — likely the API doesn't support pagination, returns non-JSON, or uses unsupported auth\r\n- AMA-based methods don't apply to REST API sources\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Requires custom code (Azure Function, Logic App, or script) to call the source API\r\n- You must manage the DCE + DCR + Entra app registration\r\n- Polling frequency and data transformation are your responsibility",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4a",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultLogsAPI"
          },
          {
            "type": 9,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
              "parameters": [
                {
                  "id": "8c110668-7163-43ad-b235-f4c32a343a15",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "Q4b",
                  "label": "4️⃣b Does the data need preprocessing or transformation?",
                  "type": 10,
                  "isRequired": true,
                  "typeSettings": {
                    "additionalResourceOptions": [],
                    "showDefault": false
                  },
                  "jsonData": "[{ \"value\": \"Yes\", \"label\": \"Yes\"},\r\n {\"value\": \"No\", \"label\": \"No\" }]",
                  "timeContext": {
                    "durationMs": 86400000
                  }
                }
              ],
              "style": "formVertical",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q3",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "param-Q4b-Preprocessing"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "*💡 Consider this if logs need parsing, enrichment, filtering, or format conversion before ingestion. Both Azure Monitor Pipeline and Logstash handle CEF, Syslog, and custom formats.*"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q3",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "text-HelpQ4b"
          },
          {
            "type": 9,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
              "parameters": [
                {
                  "id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "Q4c",
                  "label": "4️⃣c Do you have an Arc-enabled Kubernetes cluster available?",
                  "type": 10,
                  "isRequired": true,
                  "typeSettings": {
                    "additionalResourceOptions": [],
                    "showDefault": false
                  },
                  "jsonData": "[{ \"value\": \"Yes\", \"label\": \"Yes\"},\r\n {\"value\": \"No\", \"label\": \"No\" }]",
                  "timeContext": {
                    "durationMs": 86400000
                  }
                }
              ],
              "style": "formVertical",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q4b",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "param-Q4c-K8s"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "*💡 Azure Monitor Pipeline runs on Arc-enabled K8s and is the Microsoft-native alternative to Logstash — it auto-schematizes Syslog/CEF, supports persistent buffering, and requires no third-party components.*"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q4b",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "text-HelpQ4c"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Azure Monitor Pipeline\r\n\r\nAzure Monitor Pipeline is a containerized, Microsoft-native solution that runs on an Arc-enabled Kubernetes cluster. It receives Syslog, CEF, and OTLP telemetry, applies filtering/transformation locally, and forwards data to Azure Monitor.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Arc-enabled Kubernetes cluster with cert-manager extension\r\n- Custom locations enabled on the cluster\r\n- Data Collection Endpoint (DCE) + Data Collection Rule (DCR)\r\n- Log Analytics workspace (with Sentinel for CommonSecurityLog)\r\n\r\n**Key advantages over Logstash:**\r\n- Auto-schematizes to `Syslog` and `CommonSecurityLog` tables\r\n- Persistent local storage survives connectivity loss\r\n- No third-party software to license or maintain\r\n- Built-in TLS/mTLS support\r\n\r\n🔗 [Azure Monitor Pipeline overview](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/data-collection/pipeline-overview)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), needs preprocessing (Q4b: {Q4b}), and you have an Arc-enabled K8s cluster (Q4c: {Q4c}). Azure Monitor Pipeline is the Microsoft-native choice for centralized log processing.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- Logstash would work but requires third-party software licensing and maintenance\r\n- Direct AMA (CEF/Syslog) doesn't provide preprocessing capabilities\r\n- CCF/Logs API require a REST API (you answered No)\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Requires Arc-enabled Kubernetes cluster with cert-manager extension\r\n- Currently supports Syslog, CEF, and OTLP — other formats may not be supported yet\r\n- You are responsible for operating the Kubernetes environment",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4b",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4c",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultPipeline"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Logstash with Sentinel Output Plugin\r\n\r\nUse Logstash for data preprocessing, transformation, and enrichment before sending to Microsoft Sentinel. Suitable when no Kubernetes cluster is available.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Logstash instance (existing or new)\r\n- Microsoft Sentinel output plugin (`microsoft-sentinel-log-analytics-logstash-output-plugin`)\r\n- Data Collection Endpoint (DCE) + Data Collection Rule (DCR)\r\n\r\n🔗 [Connect Logstash to Sentinel](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/connect-logstash-data-connection-rules)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), needs preprocessing (Q4b: {Q4b}), but no Arc-enabled K8s cluster is available (Q4c: {Q4c}). Logstash is the established fallback for preprocessing without Kubernetes.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- Azure Monitor Pipeline is preferred but requires K8s (you answered No)\r\n- Direct AMA (CEF/Syslog) doesn't provide preprocessing\r\n- CCF/Logs API require a REST API\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Logstash is open-source but Elastic licensing applies to newer versions\r\n- Requires a dedicated VM or container to run\r\n- You manage plugin updates, pipeline configs, and monitoring yourself",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4b",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4c",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultLogstash"
          },
          {
            "type": 9,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
              "parameters": [
                {
                  "id": "0f9aa3f6-a67e-4459-b2c9-ddfde9a12bda",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "Q5",
                  "label": "5️⃣ Does the data source support CEF?",
                  "type": 10,
                  "isRequired": true,
                  "typeSettings": {
                    "additionalResourceOptions": [],
                    "showDefault": false
                  },
                  "jsonData": "[{ \"value\": \"Yes\", \"label\": \"Yes\"},\r\n {\"value\": \"No\", \"label\": \"No\" }]",
                  "timeContext": {
                    "durationMs": 86400000
                  }
                }
              ],
              "style": "formVertical",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q4b",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "param-Q5-CEF"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "*💡 Common Event Format (CEF) is widely used by firewalls, IDS/IPS, and network appliances. Check your vendor's logging documentation.*"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q4b",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "text-HelpQ5"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ CEF via AMA\r\n\r\nUse the Azure Monitor Agent (AMA) to collect Common Event Format (CEF) logs. CEF is a standard log format used by many network and security appliances.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Linux log forwarder VM with AMA installed\r\n- Data Collection Rule (DCR) for CEF\r\n- Source device configured to send CEF to the forwarder\r\n\r\n🔗 [Ingest CEF logs with AMA](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/connect-cef-ama)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), doesn't need preprocessing (Q4b: {Q4b}), and supports CEF (Q5: {Q5}). AMA with a Linux forwarder is the lightest managed path for CEF data.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- Preprocessing solutions (Pipeline/Logstash) are overkill — your data doesn't need transformation\r\n- Syslog via AMA is for non-CEF syslog — CEF is more structured and preferred when available\r\n- CCF/Logs API require a REST API\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Requires a dedicated Linux forwarder VM with AMA installed\r\n- Forwarder VM sizing affects maximum throughput\r\n- Source device must be configured to send CEF to the forwarder's IP on port 514",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4b",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q5",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultCEF"
          },
          {
            "type": 9,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
              "parameters": [
                {
                  "id": "3e445909-184a-475e-a76b-6949a09a0d2e",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "Q6",
                  "label": "6️⃣ Does it support Syslog?",
                  "type": 10,
                  "isRequired": true,
                  "typeSettings": {
                    "additionalResourceOptions": [],
                    "showDefault": false
                  },
                  "jsonData": "[{ \"value\": \"Yes\", \"label\": \"Yes\"},\r\n {\"value\": \"No\", \"label\": \"No\" }]",
                  "timeContext": {
                    "durationMs": 86400000
                  }
                }
              ],
              "style": "formVertical",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q5",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "param-Q6-Syslog"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "*💡 Syslog is the standard logging protocol for Linux systems and many network devices. Check if your device can forward syslog over TCP/UDP.*"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q5",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "text-HelpQ6"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Syslog via AMA\r\n\r\nUse the Azure Monitor Agent (AMA) to collect Syslog messages. Suitable for Linux-based appliances and services that emit standard Syslog.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Linux VM with AMA installed (or direct agent on source)\r\n- rsyslog or syslog-ng configured to forward logs\r\n- Data Collection Rule (DCR) for Syslog\r\n\r\n🔗 [Collect Syslog with AMA](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/connect-cef-syslog-ama)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), doesn't need preprocessing (Q4b: {Q4b}), doesn't support CEF (Q5: {Q5}), but supports Syslog (Q6: {Q6}). AMA handles standard Syslog natively.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- CEF via AMA was preferred but your source doesn't output CEF format\r\n- Preprocessing solutions are unnecessary — standard Syslog works as-is\r\n- CCF/Logs API require a REST API\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Requires a Linux VM with AMA (or direct agent on source if supported)\r\n- Only standard Syslog facilities and severities are supported\r\n- Custom-formatted syslog messages may need DCR transformations for proper parsing",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4b",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q5",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q6",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultSyslog"
          },
          {
            "type": 9,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
              "parameters": [
                {
                  "id": "bb5c0715-1ed9-4d1c-af4b-604f3d04731d",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "Q7",
                  "label": "7️⃣ Does the source export files (CSV/JSON)?",
                  "type": 10,
                  "isRequired": true,
                  "typeSettings": {
                    "additionalResourceOptions": [],
                    "showDefault": false
                  },
                  "jsonData": "[{ \"value\": \"Yes\", \"label\": \"Yes\"},\r\n {\"value\": \"No\", \"label\": \"No\" }]",
                  "timeContext": {
                    "durationMs": 86400000
                  }
                }
              ],
              "style": "formVertical",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q6",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "param-Q7-FileExport"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "*💡 Some systems export audit logs or event data as CSV/JSON files on a schedule. AMA can tail these files automatically.*"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q6",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "text-HelpQ7"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Custom Logs v2 — File Upload via AMA\r\n\r\nUse the Azure Monitor Agent to collect log data from text files (CSV, JSON, or custom delimited formats) on Windows or Linux machines.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- AMA installed on the machine with the log files\r\n- Custom table created in Log Analytics workspace\r\n- Data Collection Rule (DCR) with custom log source\r\n\r\n🔗 [Collect custom text logs with AMA](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/connect-custom-logs-ama)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), no preprocessing needed (Q4b: {Q4b}), no CEF (Q5: {Q5}), no Syslog (Q6: {Q6}), but exports files (Q7: {Q7}). AMA can tail CSV/JSON files directly from disk.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- All network-based methods (CEF, Syslog, Webhook) don't apply — your source exports files\r\n- Preprocessing isn't needed — the file format is usable as-is\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- AMA must be installed on the machine where files are written\r\n- Requires a custom table in Log Analytics (not a built-in table)\r\n- File rotation and cleanup are your responsibility\r\n- Not suitable for real-time alerting — depends on file write frequency",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4b",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q5",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q6",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q7",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultCustomLogs"
          },
          {
            "type": 9,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
              "parameters": [
                {
                  "id": "edc1f62c-704e-4b25-b2ab-dea42cfc3e52",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "Q8",
                  "label": "8️⃣ Does the source support webhooks?",
                  "type": 10,
                  "isRequired": true,
                  "typeSettings": {
                    "additionalResourceOptions": [],
                    "showDefault": false
                  },
                  "jsonData": "[{ \"value\": \"Yes\", \"label\": \"Yes\"},\r\n {\"value\": \"No\", \"label\": \"No\" }]",
                  "timeContext": {
                    "durationMs": 86400000
                  }
                }
              ],
              "style": "formVertical",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q7",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "param-Q8-Webhooks"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "*💡 Webhooks let the source push events in real-time to an HTTP endpoint. You'll need an Azure Function or Logic App to receive and forward them.*"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q7",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "No"
            },
            "name": "text-HelpQ8"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Webhook → Azure Function / Logic App → Logs Ingestion API\r\n\r\nConfigure the data source to push events via webhook to an Azure Function or Logic App, which then forwards data to Sentinel via the Logs Ingestion API.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Azure Function (HTTP trigger) or Logic App (HTTP trigger)\r\n- Data Collection Endpoint (DCE) + Data Collection Rule (DCR)\r\n- Webhook configuration on the source system\r\n\r\n🔗 [Logs Ingestion API overview](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/logs/logs-ingestion-api-overview)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), no preprocessing needed (Q4b: {Q4b}), no CEF (Q5: {Q5}), no Syslog (Q6: {Q6}), no file export (Q7: No), but supports webhooks (Q8: {Q8}). Event-driven push via webhook is the most responsive option left.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- All agent-based methods require protocol support your source doesn't have\r\n- File upload is not applicable — your source doesn't export files\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- You need an Azure Function or Logic App to receive and transform the webhook payload\r\n- Webhook endpoints must be internet-accessible (or use private endpoints)\r\n- Retry logic and deduplication are your responsibility\r\n- Cost scales with event volume (Function/Logic App consumption billing)",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4b",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q5",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q6",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q8",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultWebhook"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ⚠️ Ad-hoc Upload via Logs Ingestion API (Last Resort)\r\n\r\nWhen no other ingestion method is available, data can be manually or semi-automatically uploaded to Sentinel using the Logs Ingestion API. This is suitable for **low-volume, infrequent** data only.\r\n\r\n**Built on:** Data Collection Endpoint (DCE) + Data Collection Rule (DCR)\r\n\r\n**Key Notes:**\r\n- ❌ Avoid MMA/OMS agent (retired Aug 31, 2024) — use AMA\r\n- ⚠️ HTTP Data Collector API is deprecated (retires Sep 14, 2026)\r\n- Use Logs Ingestion API for all new custom integrations\r\n\r\n🔗 [Logs Ingestion API overview](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/logs/logs-ingestion-api-overview)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), no preprocessing needed (Q4b: {Q4b}), no CEF (Q5: {Q5}), no Syslog (Q6: {Q6}), no file export (Q7: No), and no webhooks (Q8: {Q8}). This is the last resort when no automated method is available.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- Every automated ingestion method has been evaluated and ruled out based on your answers above\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Manual or scripted process — not suitable for high-volume or real-time data\r\n- Requires someone to periodically extract and upload data\r\n- Consider revisiting the tree — can preprocessing (Q4b) unlock a better path via Logstash or Azure Monitor Pipeline?",
              "style": "warning"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4b",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q5",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q6",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q8",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultAdHoc"
          }
        ]
      },
      "conditionalVisibility": {
        "parameterName": "Tab",
        "comparison": "isEqualTo",
        "value": "2"
      },
      "name": "group-AlternativeIngestion"
    },
    {
      "type": 12,
      "content": {
        "version": "NotebookGroup/1.0",
        "groupType": "editable",
        "items": [
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "## Installed Data Connectors & Coverage\r\n\r\nThis tab assesses your Sentinel deployment: connector health, data freshness, deployment maturity, and security domain coverage."
            },
            "name": "text-InstalledHeader"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### 📖 How to Read This Tab\r\n\r\nThis tab assesses your **deployment maturity** — not by counting connectors against the full 600+ catalog (which would always look low), but by classifying your deployment against real-world benchmarks.\r\n\r\n**Deployment Maturity** uses two signals:\r\n- **Installed count** — how many connectors are reporting health data in the last 7 days\r\n- **Domains Covered** — how many of the 11 security domains (Identity, Endpoint, Network, Cloud, Email, Threat Intelligence, etc.) have at least one active connector\r\n\r\n> *\"While Microsoft Sentinel supports 600+ connectors, productive enterprise deployments typically operationalize around 15–40 connectors, scaling higher in mature SOC environments depending on data sources and use-case maturity.\"*\r\n\r\n**What matters more than connector count:**\r\n- ✅ Are **high-value sources** onboarded? (Entra ID, Defender XDR, firewall logs)\r\n- ✅ Are **key security domains** covered? (Identity + Endpoint + Network + Cloud at minimum)\r\n- ✅ Is ingestion **optimized**? (no duplication, no noise, right retention tier)\r\n- ❌ Avoid maximizing connector count — it increases cost and noise without proportional security value\r\n\r\n**Data source:** All health and freshness data comes from the `SentinelHealth` table (last 7 days). Domain coverage is computed by matching installed connectors against the connector catalog watchlist (`Con`).\r\n\r\n**📋 Recommendations** below the summary metrics automatically surfaces coverage gaps (domains with zero or minimal connectors), connector health issues (failures and warnings), and stale data sources. Items are prioritized by severity — address 🔴 High items first.\r\n\r\n🔗 [Best practices for data collection](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/best-practices-data)",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Help",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "text-InstalledHelp"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "let installedRaw = SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| distinct SentinelResourceName;\r\nlet installedCount = toscalar(installedRaw | count);\r\nlet installed = installedRaw\r\n| extend Keys = pack_array(\r\n    tolower(SentinelResourceName),\r\n    tolower(extract(\"^(.+?)-[^-]+$\", 1, SentinelResourceName)),\r\n    replace_regex(tolower(SentinelResourceName), \"connector$\", \"\"))\r\n| mv-expand InstalledKey = Keys to typeof(string)\r\n| where isnotempty(InstalledKey)\r\n| distinct InstalledKey;\r\nlet catalog = _GetWatchlist('Con')\r\n| project\r\n    ConnectorID = column_ifexists(\"Connector ID\", \"\"),\r\n    Domain      = column_ifexists(\"Domain\", \"Other\")\r\n| extend CatalogKey = tolower(ConnectorID);\r\nlet domainsCovered = toscalar(\r\n    catalog\r\n    | join kind=inner installed on $left.CatalogKey == $right.InstalledKey\r\n    | mv-expand SingleDomain = split(Domain, \",\") to typeof(string)\r\n    | extend SingleDomain = trim(\" \", SingleDomain)\r\n    | where SingleDomain != \"Other\"\r\n    | summarize by SingleDomain\r\n    | count\r\n);\r\nlet tier = case(\r\n    installedCount >= 80, \"🟣 Enterprise\",\r\n    installedCount >= 40, \"🟢 Mature SOC\",\r\n    installedCount >= 15, \"🔵 Productive\",\r\n    installedCount >= 5,  \"🟡 Early\",\r\n    \"⚪ Initial\");\r\nprint\r\n    Installed = installedCount,\r\n    Maturity = tier,\r\n    ['Domains Covered'] = strcat(tostring(domainsCovered), ' / 11')",
              "size": 4,
              "title": "Deployment Maturity",
              "timeContext": {
                "durationMs": 604800000
              },
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
              "visualization": "cards",
              "chartSettings": {
                "showMetrics": false
              }
            },
            "customWidth": "33",
            "name": "query-CoverageSummary"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| summarize LastStatus = arg_max(TimeGenerated, Status) by SentinelResourceName\r\n| summarize Count = count() by Status\r\n| sort by Count desc",
              "size": 4,
              "title": "Health Summary",
              "timeContext": {
                "durationMs": 604800000
              },
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
              "visualization": "piechart"
            },
            "customWidth": "33",
            "name": "query-HealthPieChart"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| summarize LastEvent = max(TimeGenerated) by SentinelResourceName\r\n| extend FreshnessBucket = case(\r\n    LastEvent > ago(1h), \"< 1 hour\",\r\n    LastEvent > ago(24h), \"< 24 hours\",\r\n    LastEvent > ago(3d), \"< 3 days\",\r\n    \"3+ days (stale)\"\r\n    )\r\n| summarize Count = count() by FreshnessBucket\r\n| sort by Count desc",
              "size": 4,
              "title": "Data Freshness",
              "timeContext": {
                "durationMs": 604800000
              },
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
              "visualization": "piechart"
            },
            "customWidth": "33",
            "name": "query-FreshnessPieChart"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### 📊 Deployment Maturity Tiers\r\n\r\n| Tier | Connectors | Profile |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| ⚪ Initial | <5 | Pilot or POC phase |\r\n| 🟡 Early | 5–15 | Core Microsoft signals (Entra, Defender, M365) |\r\n| 🔵 Productive | 15–40 | Microsoft + network + identity + SaaS coverage |\r\n| 🟢 Mature SOC | 40–80 | Multi-vendor, custom connectors, TI feeds |\r\n| 🟣 Enterprise | 80+ | MSSP, multi-cloud, OT/IoT, full spectrum |\r\n\r\nℹ️ *More connectors ≠ better security. Value is driven by coverage of key domains and use-case alignment with detection rules.*",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Help",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "text-MaturityLegend"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### 📋 Recommendations Legend\r\n\r\n| Priority | Category | What triggers it |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| 🔴 High | 🛡️ Coverage Gap | A security domain has 0 installed connectors |\r\n| 🔴 High | ❌ Connector Failure | A connector reported failure events in the last 7 days |\r\n| 🟡 Medium | 🛡️ Minimal Coverage | A domain has only 1 connector (single point of failure) |\r\n| 🟡 Medium | ⚠️ Connector Warning | A connector reported warning events |\r\n| 🟡 Medium | 🕐 Stale Data | A connector's last health event is 3+ days old |\r\n\r\nℹ️ *Recommendations are dynamically generated from SentinelHealth and the connector catalog. An empty table means no issues were detected.*",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Help",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "text-RecommendationsLegend"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "let installed = SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| distinct SentinelResourceName\r\n| extend Keys = pack_array(\r\n    tolower(SentinelResourceName),\r\n    tolower(extract(\"^(.+?)-[^-]+$\", 1, SentinelResourceName)),\r\n    replace_regex(tolower(SentinelResourceName), \"connector$\", \"\"))\r\n| mv-expand InstalledKey = Keys to typeof(string)\r\n| where isnotempty(InstalledKey)\r\n| distinct InstalledKey;\r\nlet catalog = _GetWatchlist('Con')\r\n| project\r\n    ConnectorID = column_ifexists(\"Connector ID\", \"\"),\r\n    Domain      = column_ifexists(\"Domain\", \"Other\")\r\n| extend CatalogKey = tolower(ConnectorID);\r\nlet coverageGaps = catalog\r\n| join kind=leftouter installed on $left.CatalogKey == $right.InstalledKey\r\n| extend IsInstalled = isnotempty(InstalledKey)\r\n| mv-expand SingleDomain = split(Domain, \",\") to typeof(string)\r\n| extend Domain = trim(\" \", SingleDomain)\r\n| where Domain != \"Other\"\r\n| summarize Total = count(), Installed = countif(IsInstalled) by Domain\r\n| where Installed == 0\r\n| project\r\n    Priority = 'High',\r\n    Category = 'Coverage Gap',\r\n    Finding = strcat('Domain \"', Domain, '\" has no installed connectors (0/', tostring(Total), ' available)'),\r\n    Action = strcat('Open Security Coverage by Domain & Subdomain and onboard at least one key source in \"', Domain, '\"');\r\nlet minimalCoverage = catalog\r\n| join kind=leftouter installed on $left.CatalogKey == $right.InstalledKey\r\n| extend IsInstalled = isnotempty(InstalledKey)\r\n| mv-expand SingleDomain = split(Domain, \",\") to typeof(string)\r\n| extend Domain = trim(\" \", SingleDomain)\r\n| where Domain != \"Other\"\r\n| summarize Total = count(), Installed = countif(IsInstalled) by Domain\r\n| where Installed == 1\r\n| project\r\n    Priority = 'Medium',\r\n    Category = 'Minimal Coverage',\r\n    Finding = strcat('Domain \"', Domain, '\" has only 1 connector installed (1/', tostring(Total), ' available)'),\r\n    Action = 'Add a second connector to eliminate single point of failure';\r\nlet healthIssues = SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| where Status in (\"Failure\", \"Warning\")\r\n| summarize Count = count(), LastSeen = max(TimeGenerated) by SentinelResourceName, Status\r\n| project\r\n    Priority = iff(Status == \"Failure\", 'High', 'Medium'),\r\n    Category = iff(Status == \"Failure\", 'Connector Failure', 'Connector Warning'),\r\n    Finding = strcat(SentinelResourceName, ' — ', tostring(Count), ' ', tolower(Status), ' event(s), last seen ', format_datetime(LastSeen, 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm')),\r\n    Action = iff(Status == \"Failure\", 'Investigate connector configuration and data source connectivity', 'Open Connector Health Details and review Recent Failures & Warnings');\r\nlet staleConnectors = SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| summarize LastEvent = max(TimeGenerated) by SentinelResourceName\r\n| where LastEvent < ago(3d)\r\n| project\r\n    Priority = 'Medium',\r\n    Category = 'Stale Data',\r\n    Finding = strcat(SentinelResourceName, ' — last health event ', format_datetime(LastEvent, 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm'), ' (3+ days ago)'),\r\n    Action = 'Verify the data source is still active and sending data';\r\nunion coverageGaps, healthIssues, minimalCoverage, staleConnectors\r\n| sort by Priority asc, Category asc",
              "size": 3,
              "title": "📋 Recommendations",
              "timeContext": {
                "durationMs": 604800000
              },
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
              "visualization": "table",
              "gridSettings": {
                "rowLimit": 50,
                "formatters": [
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Priority",
                    "formatter": 18,
                    "formatOptions": {
                      "thresholdsOptions": "icons",
                      "thresholdsGrid": [
                        {
                          "operator": "contains",
                          "thresholdValue": "High",
                          "representation": "4",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        },
                        {
                          "operator": "Default",
                          "thresholdValue": "",
                          "representation": "2",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Category",
                    "formatter": 18,
                    "formatOptions": {
                      "thresholdsOptions": "icons",
                      "thresholdsGrid": [
                        {
                          "operator": "contains",
                          "thresholdValue": "Failure",
                          "representation": "4",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        },
                        {
                          "operator": "contains",
                          "thresholdValue": "Coverage Gap",
                          "representation": "Sev1",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        },
                        {
                          "operator": "contains",
                          "thresholdValue": "Warning",
                          "representation": "2",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        },
                        {
                          "operator": "contains",
                          "thresholdValue": "Stale",
                          "representation": "1",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        },
                        {
                          "operator": "Default",
                          "thresholdValue": "",
                          "representation": "more",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "noDataMessage": "✅ No issues detected — all domains covered and connectors healthy."
              }
            },
            "name": "query-Recommendations"
          },
          {
            "type": 12,
            "content": {
              "version": "NotebookGroup/1.0",
              "groupType": "editable",
              "title": "Connector Health Details",
              "expandable": true,
              "expanded": false,
              "items": [
                {
                  "type": 3,
                  "content": {
                    "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
                    "query": "SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| summarize \r\n    LastEvent = max(TimeGenerated),\r\n    HealthStatus = arg_max(TimeGenerated, Status)\r\n    by SentinelResourceName, SentinelResourceKind\r\n| extend Freshness = case(\r\n    LastEvent > ago(1h), \"< 1 hour\",\r\n    LastEvent > ago(24h), \"< 24 hours\",\r\n    LastEvent > ago(3d), \"< 3 days\",\r\n    \"3+ days\"\r\n    )\r\n| project \r\n    ['Connector Name'] = SentinelResourceName,\r\n    Kind = SentinelResourceKind,\r\n    ['Last Status'] = Status,\r\n    ['Last Event'] = LastEvent,\r\n    Freshness\r\n| sort by ['Connector Name'] asc",
                    "size": 1,
                    "title": "Connector Health Status (Last 7 Days)",
                    "timeContext": {
                      "durationMs": 604800000
                    },
                    "queryType": 0,
                    "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
                    "visualization": "table",
                    "gridSettings": {
                      "rowLimit": 500,
                      "formatters": [
                        {
                          "columnMatch": "Last Status",
                          "formatter": 18,
                          "formatOptions": {
                            "thresholdsOptions": "icons",
                            "thresholdsGrid": [
                              {
                                "operator": "==",
                                "thresholdValue": "Failure",
                                "representation": "4",
                                "text": "{0}{1}"
                              },
                              {
                                "operator": "==",
                                "thresholdValue": "Warning",
                                "representation": "2",
                                "text": "{0}{1}"
                              },
                              {
                                "operator": "==",
                                "thresholdValue": "Informational",
                                "representation": "1",
                                "text": "{0}{1}"
                              },
                              {
                                "operator": "Default",
                                "thresholdValue": "",
                                "representation": "success",
                                "text": "{0}{1}"
                              }
                            ]
                          }
                        }
                      ],
                      "noDataMessage": "No connector health data found. Ensure auditing and health monitoring is enabled."
                    }
                  },
                  "name": "query-ConnectorHealth"
                },
                {
                  "type": 3,
                  "content": {
                    "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
                    "query": "SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| where Status in (\"Failure\", \"Warning\")\r\n| summarize \r\n    Count = count(),\r\n    LastOccurrence = max(TimeGenerated)\r\n    by SentinelResourceName, Status, Description\r\n| sort by LastOccurrence desc",
                    "size": 4,
                    "title": "⚠️ Recent Failures & Warnings",
                    "timeContext": {
                      "durationMs": 604800000
                    },
                    "queryType": 0,
                    "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
                    "visualization": "table",
                    "gridSettings": {
                      "rowLimit": 100,
                      "noDataMessage": "✅ No recent connector failures or warnings detected."
                    }
                  },
                  "name": "query-FailuresWarnings"
                }
              ]
            },
            "name": "group-ConnectorHealthDetails"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### 🗂️ Security Domain Taxonomy\r\n\r\n| Domain | Subdomains |\r\n|---|---|\r\n| **Identity** | Authentication & SSO · Privileged Access · Identity Threat Protection |\r\n| **Email** | Email Platform · Email Security |\r\n| **Endpoint** | Detection & Response · Endpoint Protection · Vulnerability Management |\r\n| **Cloud Control Plane** | Activity & Audit Logs · Cloud Security Posture · Secrets & Compliance |\r\n| **Network / Perimeter** | Firewall & Gateway · Web & DNS Security · Network Detection |\r\n| **Threat Intelligence** | TI Feeds & Platforms · Threat Analytics |\r\n| **OT / IoT Security** | Industrial Control Systems · IoT & Device Security |\r\n| **Data Security** | Data Loss Prevention · Backup & Recovery |\r\n| **SIEM & Orchestration** | Aggregators & Forwarders · Automation & Response |\r\n| **Infrastructure** | Azure Platform Services · Application Servers |\r\n| **SaaS / Business Apps** | Collaboration & DevOps · Business Applications |\r\n| **Other** | Connectors not yet classified |",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Help",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "text-DomainLegend"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "let installed = SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| distinct SentinelResourceName\r\n| extend Keys = pack_array(\r\n    tolower(SentinelResourceName),\r\n    tolower(extract(\"^(.+?)-[^-]+$\", 1, SentinelResourceName)),\r\n    replace_regex(tolower(SentinelResourceName), \"connector$\", \"\"))\r\n| mv-expand InstalledKey = Keys to typeof(string)\r\n| where isnotempty(InstalledKey)\r\n| distinct InstalledKey;\r\nlet catalog = _GetWatchlist('Con')\r\n| project\r\n    ConnectorName = column_ifexists(\"Connector Name\", \"\"),\r\n    ConnectorID  = column_ifexists(\"Connector ID\", \"\"),\r\n    Domain       = column_ifexists(\"Domain\", \"Other\"),\r\n    Subdomain    = column_ifexists(\"Subdomain\", \"\")\r\n| extend CatalogKey = tolower(ConnectorID);\r\ncatalog\r\n| join kind=leftouter installed on $left.CatalogKey == $right.InstalledKey\r\n| extend Installed = isnotempty(InstalledKey)\r\n| mv-expand SingleDomain = split(Domain, \",\") to typeof(string)\r\n| extend Domain = trim(\" \", SingleDomain)\r\n| mv-expand SingleSubdomain = split(Subdomain, \",\") to typeof(string)\r\n| extend Subdomain = trim(\" \", SingleSubdomain)\r\n| summarize\r\n    Total     = count(),\r\n    Installed = countif(Installed)\r\n    by Domain, Subdomain\r\n| extend Coverage = iff(Installed > 0, 'Covered', 'Not covered')\r\n| project Domain, Subdomain, Coverage, ['Installed / Total'] = strcat(tostring(Installed), ' / ', tostring(Total))\r\n| sort by Domain asc, Coverage asc",
              "size": 2,
              "title": "🛡️ Security Coverage by Domain & Subdomain — click a row to see connectors",
              "timeContext": {
                "durationMs": 604800000
              },
              "exportFieldName": "Subdomain",
              "exportParameterName": "SelectedSubdomain",
              "exportDefaultValue": "",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
              "visualization": "table",
              "gridSettings": {
                "rowLimit": 50,
                "formatters": [
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Coverage",
                    "formatter": 18,
                    "formatOptions": {
                      "thresholdsOptions": "icons",
                      "thresholdsGrid": [
                        {
                          "operator": "contains",
                          "thresholdValue": "Not covered",
                          "representation": "4",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        },
                        {
                          "operator": "Default",
                          "thresholdValue": "",
                          "representation": "success",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            "customWidth": "70",
            "name": "query-DomainCoverageHeatmap"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "let installed = SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| distinct SentinelResourceName\r\n| extend Keys = pack_array(\r\n    tolower(SentinelResourceName),\r\n    tolower(extract(\"^(.+?)-[^-]+$\", 1, SentinelResourceName)),\r\n    replace_regex(tolower(SentinelResourceName), \"connector$\", \"\"))\r\n| mv-expand InstalledKey = Keys to typeof(string)\r\n| where isnotempty(InstalledKey)\r\n| distinct InstalledKey;\r\nlet catalog = _GetWatchlist('Con')\r\n| project\r\n    ConnectorID = column_ifexists(\"Connector ID\", \"\"),\r\n    Domain      = column_ifexists(\"Domain\", \"Other\")\r\n| extend CatalogKey = tolower(ConnectorID);\r\ncatalog\r\n| join kind=leftouter installed on $left.CatalogKey == $right.InstalledKey\r\n| extend IsInstalled = isnotempty(InstalledKey)\r\n| mv-expand SingleDomain = split(Domain, \",\") to typeof(string)\r\n| extend Domain = trim(\" \", SingleDomain)\r\n| summarize\r\n    Total = count(),\r\n    Installed = countif(IsInstalled)\r\n    by Domain\r\n| extend Status = case(\r\n    Installed == 0, '❌ Gap',\r\n    Installed == 1, '⚠️ Minimal',\r\n    Installed < 4, '🟡 Developing',\r\n    '✅ Solid')\r\n| project Domain, Status\r\n| sort by Status asc, Domain asc",
              "size": 2,
              "title": "📊 Domain Coverage Heatmap",
              "timeContext": {
                "durationMs": 604800000
              },
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
              "visualization": "table",
              "gridSettings": {
                "formatters": [
                  {
                    "columnMatch": "Status",
                    "formatter": 18,
                    "formatOptions": {
                      "thresholdsOptions": "icons",
                      "thresholdsGrid": [
                        {
                          "operator": "contains",
                          "thresholdValue": "Gap",
                          "representation": "4",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        },
                        {
                          "operator": "contains",
                          "thresholdValue": "Minimal",
                          "representation": "2",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        },
                        {
                          "operator": "contains",
                          "thresholdValue": "Developing",
                          "representation": "1",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        },
                        {
                          "operator": "Default",
                          "thresholdValue": "",
                          "representation": "success",
                          "text": "{0}{1}"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              "sortBy": []
            },
            "customWidth": "30",
            "name": "query-DomainCoverageChart"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### 🎨 Heatmap Legend\r\n\r\n| Status | Installed | Meaning |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| ❌ Gap | 0 | No connectors — domain has no coverage |\r\n| ⚠️ Minimal | 1 | Single connector — fragile, no redundancy |\r\n| 🟡 Developing | 2–3 | Growing coverage — evaluate key sources |\r\n| ✅ Solid | 4+ | Strong coverage across the domain |",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Help",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "text-HeatmapLegend"
          },
          {
            "type": 9,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
              "parameters": [
                {
                  "id": "f1a2b3c4-d5e6-7890-abcd-ef0123456789",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "StatusFilter",
                  "label": "Show",
                  "type": 10,
                  "isRequired": true,
                  "typeSettings": {
                    "additionalResourceOptions": [],
                    "showDefault": false
                  },
                  "jsonData": "[{ \"value\": \"All\", \"label\": \"All\", \"selected\": true },\r\n{ \"value\": \"Installed\", \"label\": \"✅ Installed\" },\r\n{ \"value\": \"Not installed\", \"label\": \"— Not installed\" }]",
                  "timeContext": {
                    "durationMs": 86400000
                  }
                }
              ],
              "style": "above",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "SelectedSubdomain",
              "comparison": "isNotEqualTo"
            },
            "name": "param-StatusFilter"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "let selectedSubdomain = '{SelectedSubdomain}';\r\nlet installed = SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| distinct SentinelResourceName\r\n| extend Keys = pack_array(\r\n    tolower(SentinelResourceName),\r\n    tolower(extract(\"^(.+?)-[^-]+$\", 1, SentinelResourceName)),\r\n    replace_regex(tolower(SentinelResourceName), \"connector$\", \"\"))\r\n| mv-expand InstalledKey = Keys to typeof(string)\r\n| where isnotempty(InstalledKey)\r\n| distinct InstalledKey;\r\nlet catalog = _GetWatchlist('Con')\r\n| project\r\n    ConnectorName = column_ifexists(\"Connector Name\", \"\"),\r\n    ConnectorID  = column_ifexists(\"Connector ID\", \"\"),\r\n    Domain       = column_ifexists(\"Domain\", \"Other\"),\r\n    Subdomain    = column_ifexists(\"Subdomain\", \"\"),\r\n    Vendor       = column_ifexists(\"Vendor\", \"\"),\r\n    Method       = column_ifexists(\"Method\", \"\")\r\n| extend CatalogKey = tolower(ConnectorID);\r\ncatalog\r\n| join kind=leftouter installed on $left.CatalogKey == $right.InstalledKey\r\n| extend Status = iff(isnotempty(InstalledKey), \"✅ Installed\", \"— Not installed\")\r\n| mv-expand SingleSubdomain = split(Subdomain, \",\") to typeof(string)\r\n| extend SingleSubdomain = trim(\" \", SingleSubdomain)\r\n| where SingleSubdomain == selectedSubdomain\r\n| project ['Connector Name'] = ConnectorName, Vendor, Method, Domain, Status\r\n| where '{StatusFilter}' == 'All' or Status == iff('{StatusFilter}' == 'Installed', '✅ Installed', '— Not installed')\r\n| sort by Status asc, ['Connector Name'] asc",
              "size": 0,
              "title": "📋 Connectors in '{SelectedSubdomain}'",
              "timeContext": {
                "durationMs": 604800000
              },
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
              "visualization": "table",
              "gridSettings": {
                "rowLimit": 500
              }
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "SelectedSubdomain",
              "comparison": "isNotEqualTo"
            },
            "name": "query-DomainDetail"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ℹ️ Prerequisites\r\n\r\nThis tab requires **auditing and health monitoring** to be enabled in your Sentinel workspace. If the tables above are empty, follow the instructions to [Turn on auditing and health monitoring](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/enable-monitoring).",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "name": "text-HealthPrerequisites"
          }
        ]
      },
      "conditionalVisibility": {
        "parameterName": "Tab",
        "comparison": "isEqualTo",
        "value": "3"
      },
      "name": "group-InstalledConnectors"
    }
